[[Category:Cognitive science]]

'''Cyber Storm II''' was an international [[cyber security]] [[Military simulation|exercise]] sponsored by the [[United States]] [[Department of Homeland Security]] in 2008. The week-long exercise was centered in [[Washington, DC]] and concluded on March 15.<ref>Ian Grant. [http://www.computerweekly.com/Articles/2008/03/18/229909/cyber-storm-2-exercise-reveals-security-preparedness.htm "Cyber Storm 2 exercise reveals security preparedness"] ''[[Computerweekly.com]]''. Accessed March 21, 2008.</ref>
